me":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice de Hebden was born in 1152, in Yorkshire, England as the daughter of Uchtred fitz Dolphin of Coniston and Burnsall. She married Elias de Rilston I in 1165, in Rylstone, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 5 sons and 2 daughters. She died in 1186, in Rillington, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 34."},"et":{"1152–1186":"1152–1186","1125–1200":"1125–1200","1167–Male":"1167–Surnud","1171–Male":"1171–Surnud","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1152–1182":"1152–1182","1155–1222":"1155–1222","–1228":"–1228","–Female":"Surnud","1100–1180":"1100–1180","1165":"1165","1186":"1186","1175":"1175","1152":"1152","1182":"1182","1171":"1171","1180":"1180","1228":"1228","1125":"1125","1222":"1222","1167":"1167","1200":"1200","1100":"1100","1155":"1155","about 1155":"umbes 1155","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Rylstone, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Rylstone, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rylstone, Yorkshire, England":"Rylstone, Yorkshire, England","Hebden, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hebden, North Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rillington